The paper discusses the problem of robot manipulation in cluttered and unstructured environments, which is a common topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm involves selecting actions based on a hypothesis set, which is a common approach in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves detecting and localizing objects in the environment, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a hypothesis set and the learning of a policy also suggest a connection to reinforcement learning and decision making (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the dynamics of objects in the environment and how they react to contact, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
